# E2E Test Generation

Follow `AI_TEST_RULES.md` before adding or changing tests.

Core rules:

- Import `test` and `expect` from `@Tests/utils/fixtures/playwright-fixtures`.
- Keep specs under `tests/e2e-specs/{domain}`.
- Keep Page Objects under `tests/page-objects/{domain}`.
- Put locators in Page Objects, not in specs.
- Use `CommonPO` for shared components and behaviour.
- Use `sub-classes` for modals, tabs and reusable UI fragments.
- Register every Page Object used by specs in `tests/utils/fixtures/playwright-fixtures.ts`.
- Use destructured object arguments for every function or method that takes arguments.
- Prefer `getByTestId`, then `getByRole`, then `getByLabel` or `getByPlaceholder`; do not use CSS selectors.
- When selecting by visible text or accessible name, add `exact: true` whenever possible.
- First establish a reliable database or backend API connection so tests can perform CRUD operations for state generation and cleanup.
- Treat `ApiManager` and example services as illustrative only; adapt API calls per project while preserving the e2e structure.
- Avoid `waitForTimeout`.
- Start all code comments with a lowercase letter.